{
  "stem": "11274.4",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we were from March-- March, April, May.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "About five to six months we were in Auschwitz I.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The same.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We're still talking '42.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because we came in March, '42.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1942.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Only it is October now, we ended up in Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in Birkenau was the same thing, details going out, only a lot harsher-- the sleeping quarters, and the beatings and things was getting-- they were more cruel and more experienced every time more transports came.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because they were using us for slave labor.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't know how useful it was, because those bricks throwing wasn't a useful job.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I said, they're just waiting for us to die off, and then other ones.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they weren't very careful with which one they killed or whoever they killed, because they could be killed by a kapo.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He could be killed by the SS guard that was with us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We marched out with a kapo that didn't have-- that was wearing a striped dress like we were.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "By the way, we got-- at one point in Birkenau, they took away the Russian uniforms, and they changed us to burlap dresses, a long dress with long sleeves and buttoned up all along.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that-- for that year, the end of this year, the whole winter, we were just in that dress without underwear, without anything, and just in those wooden shoes-- we were working, again, in the details, the same as the other ones before.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't try to get in because, first place, I was Polish Jew, and I didn't have any relatives or family.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "All the Jews there, the Jewish girls that had positions were the first ones, the Slovakian.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the Slovakian girls had their cousins, had their sisters, had their-- and they gave them the positions.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
